---
When logging in this codebase (WatchAgent — app/services/, app/api/, app/repositories/):

LOGGER SETUP
- Always use structlog.get_logger(__name__) at module level. Never use print() or
  stdlib logging.info/warning/error directly in application code.
- stdlib logging.basicConfig() in poller_main.py is intentional — it wires
  third-party libraries into the structured pipeline. Do not remove it.

CONTEXT BINDING — bind before logging, not at the log call:
  - In app/services/poller.py:        bind(city=city, component="poller")
  - In app/services/weather_client.py: bind(city=city, component="weather_client")
  - In app/api/main.py middleware:     bind(request_id=uuid, method=method, path=path)
  - In app/repositories/:              no binding needed (caller provides context)

LOG LEVELS — use these exact levels for these exact conditions:
  DEBUG:   raw Open-Meteo API response body (event key: "api_response_raw",
           field: body=response.text)
  INFO:    reading inserted successfully (event key: "reading_stored",
           fields: city, timestamp, duplicate=False)
           reading skipped as duplicate (event key: "reading_skipped",
           fields: city, timestamp, duplicate=True)
           event fired and persisted (event key: "event_fired",
           fields: city, event_type, timestamp, summary)
           API request completed (event key: "request_completed",
           fields: status_code, duration_ms)
           DB tables created (event key: "db_init_complete")
  WARNING: Open-Meteo poll failed after all retries (event key: "poll_failed",
           fields: city (str), http_status (int|None), attempt_count (int),
           error_msg (str)). This is the ONLY warning type in the hot path.
  ERROR:   Unexpected exception in _handle_reading, event persistence, or DB init
           (event key: "reading_handle_failed", "event_persist_failed",
           "db_init_failed"). ALL ERROR logs must include exc_info=True.

RULES:
- Duplicate readings (IntegrityError) are INFO with duplicate=True, never WARNING or ERROR.
- poll_failed must always carry all four fields: city, http_status, attempt_count, error_msg.
  http_status is None when the failure is not an HTTP status error (timeout, DNS, etc.).
- Every ERROR log must include exc_info=True so the stack trace is captured.
- Never log sensitive data (database credentials, API keys) at any level.
